sql:
SELECT dblabel, description
FROM cell_types
ORDER BY dblabel;

SELECT short_dblabel
FROM cell_types
ORDER BY short_dblabel ASC;

external_knowledge:
- The hierarchy level represents the position of a cell type in the overall structure, with top-level cell types having a level of 1; 
- The cumulative access count includes all accesses for a cell type and its descendants in the hierarchy; 
- "Cumulative access count" refers to the total number of times a cell type, including its subtypes, has been accessed.
